#: src/2296-option-replace.md:6
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:9
msgid ""
"This RFC proposes the addition of `Option::replace` to complete the `Option::"
"take` method, it replaces the actual value in the option by `Some` with the "
"value given in parameter, returning the old value if present, without "
"deinitializing either one."
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:11
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:14
msgid ""
"You can see the `Option` as a container and other containers already have "
"this kind of method to change a value in-place like the [HashMap::replace]"
"(https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/collections/struct.HashSet.html#method."
"replace) method."
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:16
msgid ""
"How do you replace a value inside an `Option`, you can use `mem::replace` "
"but it can be really inconvenient to import the `mem` module just for that. "
"Why not adding a useful method to do that ?"
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:18
msgid "This is the symmetry of the already present `Option::take` method."
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:20
msgid "Detailed design"
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:23
msgid ""
"This method will be added to the `core::option::Option` type implementation:"
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:29
msgid "// ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:37
msgid "Drawbacks"
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:40
msgid "It increases the size of the standard library by a tiny bit."
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:42
msgid ""
"The add of this method could be a breaking change in the case of an already "
"implemented method on the `Option` enum with the `replace` name. (i.e. a "
"Trait defining the `replace` method that has been implemented on the "
"`Option` type)."
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:44
msgid ""
"This method behavior could be misinterpreted: Updating the `Option` only if "
"the variant is `Some`, doing nothing if its `None`. This other method could "
"exist too and be named `map_in_place` or `modify`, no method having this "
"kind of behavior already exist in the Rust std library."
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:46
msgid "Alternatives"
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:49
msgid ""
"Don't use the `replace` name and use `give` instead in symmetry with the "
"actual `take` method."
msgstr ""

#: src/2296-option-replace.md:50
msgid "Use directly `mem::replace`."
msgstr ""

